            <p>
                Authentication is the process of verifying the identity of a user. In a Node.js application, Passport is a popular authentication middleware that simplifies the process of implementing various authentication strategies.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Passport</strong> is a Node.js library that provides a simple, flexible, and modular way to add authentication to your web applications. It supports multiple authentication strategies, making it easy to implement local authentication (username and password) as well as third-party authentication using OAuth.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Passport-Local</strong> is a Passport strategy for authenticating with a username and password. It's commonly used for traditional username and password-based authentication.
            </p>
            <p>
                <strong>Passport-Google-OAuth</strong> is a Passport strategy for authenticating with Google using OAuth 2.0. It allows users to sign up and sign in using their Google accounts, providing a secure and convenient authentication method.
